```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return replace(lowercase(strip(col)), [" ", "-"] => "_")
end
```

This function takes a `String` as input and returns the cleaned version of the column name. It first strips any leading or trailing whitespaces using `strip`, then lowercases the entire string with `lowercase`. Finally, it replaces any spaces (`" "`) and hyphens (`"-"`) with an underscore (`"_"`) using `replace` with a dictionary as its second argument.
